00:18:37,992 --> 00:18:39,993
There's a set of diodes
on the vat's control panel,

503
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:41,203
a blue one and a red one.

504
00:18:41,287 --> 00:18:43,288
Oh, god, what kind of world is this?
I didn't ask to be born.

505
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:46,124
I need you to connect
the blue one to my left temple

506
00:18:46,209 --> 00:18:48,168
and the red one to...
Why doesn't anyone really like me?

507
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:50,170
- Focus, Grandpa!
- Just put the stupid wires on my head!

508
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,963
I hate being a teenager!

509
00:19:00,056 --> 00:19:01,807
Ugh! Arrgghh!

510
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:07,187
Ah! Uhhhhh!

511
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:09,564
Jerry, you can't bend metal.

512
00:19:09,649 --> 00:19:11,650
Then make a me that can!
How can I do that...

513
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:14,361
while I'm watching you
totally fail to bend metal?

514
00:19:14,445 --> 00:19:15,904
Good old Beth!

515
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:17,948
The mind of a robot
and the heart of an insect!

516
00:19:18,032 --> 00:19:19,783
Don't talk that way about her!

517
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:21,910
What?

518
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:24,287
Oh, it hurts!

519
00:19:24,372 --> 00:19:25,580
Oh, god.

520
00:19:28,501 --> 00:19:29,918
Stop.

521
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:33,672
This representation
displeases me.

522
00:19:33,756 --> 00:19:35,465
Aaah!

523
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:41,805
Good lord. How did you...?

524
00:19:42,056 --> 00:19:43,682
Well, I had a feeling
that, in your mind,

525
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:45,517
the ideal version of me
is one smart enough

526
00:19:45,601 --> 00:19:47,269
to see you as...

527
00:19:47,353 --> 00:19:48,854
a goddess.

528
00:19:49,105 --> 00:19:51,231
Not such a stupid worm
now, are you?

529
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:53,942
Honey, when it comes
to the subject of your ego,

530
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,986
I'm Stephen fucking Hawkinson.

531
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:58,530
Ugh, it's... Never mind.

532
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,323
I love you.

533
00:20:00,408 --> 00:20:03,827
[ PROCESSING, POWERING UP ]

534
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:05,662
[ BUZZ ]

535
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,874
- Rick!
- Pants!

536
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:11,001
Holy shit! Thanks, kids.

537
00:20:11,085 --> 00:20:13,128
You figured it out.
Well, Summer did.

538
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:15,213
Kind of weird that
you were that willing

539
00:20:15,298 --> 00:20:17,299
to sell my existence out
for some trim, Morty.

540
00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:18,842
- What?!
- Pants!

541
00:20:19,093 --> 00:20:20,802
But listen... I forgive you both
because you know what?

542
00:20:20,887 --> 00:20:22,721
I learned, today,
something important...

543
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:24,431
The teenage mind
is its own worst enemy.

544
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:25,724
Oh, I also learned this...

545
00:20:25,808 --> 00:20:27,601
[ BEEPING ]

546
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:30,687
Operation Phoenix is not
the fallback I thought it would be.

547
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:32,439
I guess it's back
to the drawing board.

548
00:20:32,523 --> 00:20:33,982
Oh, my god!

549
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,358
Oh, my god!

550
00:20:35,443 --> 00:20:38,236
- Oh, my god.
- Put some pants on!

551
00:20:38,321 --> 00:20:39,487
Put pants on.

552
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:41,448
Grandpa's back, baby!

553
00:20:41,532 --> 00:20:42,657
Grandpa's... [ BUZZ ]

554
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:44,576
Oh, man, I gotta pick up
your parents.

555
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,494
They have been blowin' me up.

556
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:47,704
One last swing for the road!

557
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:49,331
Aaaaaaaaaaah!

558
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:50,832
For the love of god,
get dressed!

559
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:55,462
So, what do you think?
You wanna...

560
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:57,213
keep this marriage
going a while longer?

561
00:20:57,298 --> 00:21:00,717
At least until Morty has
graduated high school.

562
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:02,427
Oh. Mm.

563
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:04,554
[ MOANING LIGHTLY ]

564
00:21:04,639 --> 00:21:06,765
Aha, you see?
What did I tell you two?

565
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:08,141
It worked.

566
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:09,726
You know what, Rick?
I guess, in a way...

567
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,937
Already lost interest.
Get in the car.

568
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:13,480
I've been inside a kid
all day and, now,

569
00:21:13,564 --> 00:21:15,023
I can feel my bones
scraping each other.

570
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:17,233
Uh, just so you're prepared,

571
00:21:17,318 --> 00:21:19,235
there's a bunch of dead mes
in the garage.

572
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:22,656
Huh! Sounds like our stories
were connected by a theme.

573
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:24,908
- [ LAUGHTER ]
- Not really, Jerry.

574
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:28,286
Probably a cosmetic connection
your mind mistakes for thematic.

575
00:21:28,371 --> 00:21:29,788
Oh.

576
00:21:29,872 --> 00:21:31,873
Old Rick! Ruinin' everything!

577
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:33,625
♪♪

578
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:05,156
[ SQUEAKING ]

579
00:22:05,241 --> 00:22:07,075
[ OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS ]

580
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:08,910
- Master.
- Speak.

581
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:12,080
Coach Feratu's presence was
discovered by the humans.

582
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:14,416
He has been destroyed.
No bother.

583
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,084
The mortals shall soon...

584
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,293
I'm sorry, what did you
say his name was?

585
00:22:17,378 --> 00:22:19,212
- Coach Feratu.
- Coach Feratu.

586
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:21,548
That was his real name,
like his actual vampire name?

587
00:22:21,632 --> 00:22:23,675
No no no no. His vampire
name was Balik Alistane.

588
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,385
Why the fuck
would he name himself

589
00:22:25,469 --> 00:22:27,220
after a famous vampire movie?
Was he doing a bit?

590
00:22:27,304 --> 00:22:28,555
I do not know, your unholiness.

591
00:22:28,639 --> 00:22:30,265
Jesus fucking Christ.

592
00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:32,809
From now on, no more of
this clever-name bullshit.

593
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:34,477
When a vampire is pretending
to be a human,

594
00:22:34,562 --> 00:22:35,770
they can just call themselves

595
00:22:35,855 --> 00:22:37,605
Alan Jefferson
or something like that.

596
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:38,982
It's crazy, right?

597
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:40,358
I mean, am I being an asshole?

598
00:22:40,443 --> 00:22:41,985
Okay, I feel like
everybody in the room

599
00:22:42,069 --> 00:22:43,236
is looking at me like
I'm the buzzkill.

600
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,320
I'm not?

601
00:22:44,405 --> 00:22:47,782
Good. Okay. Great. [ HISS ]

602
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:49,284
[ SCREAMING ]

603
00:22:49,368 --> 00:22:50,785
Did you get any of that?

604
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:52,787
It's-a good-a show!

